description:
Read POW_DIFFICULTY environment variable in relay/src/main.rs and apply to AppState.

What: One new env var; call state.set_pow_difficulty() after AppState::new().

Algorithm:
1. After AppState::new() in main():
   let pow_difficulty: u8 = std::env::var('POW_DIFFICULTY')
       .ok()
       .and_then(|v| v.parse::<u8>().ok())
       .unwrap_or(0);  // 0 = disabled by default (safe default for relay operators)
2. Validate: if pow_difficulty > 0 && pow_difficulty < 20 {
       tracing::warn!(pow_difficulty, 'POW_DIFFICULTY is below minimum 20; using 20');
       state.set_pow_difficulty(20);
   } else {
       state.set_pow_difficulty(pow_difficulty);
   }
3. Log: tracing::info!(pow_difficulty, 'PoW enrollment gate configured');

Defensive programming:
- 0 is a safe default — no PoW required; relay operates as before
- Parse failure silently defaults to 0 (not a hard error)
- Values 1-19 clamped to 20 with a warning
- Values > 30 accepted (but verify_token will reject them client-side; relay operator misconfiguration)
